06179nam a22008775i 9783035624243DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20222022sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356242437 a10.1515/97830356242432doi  a(DE-B1597)579433  a(OCoLC)1334343975  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0100002bisacsh04a720.4700aCoping with Urban Climates :bComparative Perspectives on Architecture and Thermal Governance /ced. by Sascha Roesler, Madlen Kobi, Lorenzo Stieger. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (240 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aKlima Polis ;v200tFrontmatter -- tMaps -- tTable of Contents -- tPreface -- tCoping with Urban Climates -- tI Urban Climates -- tGeneva (Switzerland): The Architecturalization of Water Ecologies -- tSantiago de Chile: The Standardization of Indoor-Outdoor Transitions -- tChongqing (People's Republic of China): The Electrification of the Urban Fabric -- tCairo (Egypt): The Domestication of Urban Heat -- tII Thermal Governance -- tArchitecture and Thermal Governance -- tNew Urban Climate Protocols -- tAppendices -- tEndnotes -- tReferences -- tIndex -- tAbout the Authors -- tAcknowledgments -- tIllustration Credits0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aHatte die Architektur des 20. Jahrhunderts die Kontrolle des Gebäudeklima zur Hauptaufgabe erklärt, so muss die Architektur im 21. Jahrhundert den Umgang mit dem Stadtklima lernen. Städtische Hitze und Luftverschmutzung gilt es in die Planung und Gestaltung einzubeziehen. Basierend auf empirischen Erkenntnissen aus Kairo, Chongqing, Genf und Santiago de Chile verdeutlicht das Buch, dass Materialität und soziale Praktiken, verknüpft mit Raumbeheizung, Siedlungsbegrünung, Straßenausrichtung oder Klimapolitik, das Gewebe zeitgenössischer Stadtklimata bilden. Die Publikation verbindet soziokulturelle und meteorologische Daten. Sie plädiert für eine neue Art der "Thermal Governance", die die Wechselwirkung von klimatischen und sozioökonomischen Phänomenen in zeitgenössischen Städten berücksichtigt.  aWhile 20th century architecture learned to control the climate of a building, the architecture of the 21st century needs to learn to cope with the climate of cities. Problems such as urban heat and air pollution need to be included in planning and design. Based on empirical realities in Cairo, Chongqing, Geneva and Santiago de Chile, the book underlines that the materiality and social practices attached to room heating, compound greening, street alignment or climate policies together form the tissue for contemporary urban climates. It interweaves socio-cultural with meteorological data and pioneers the new concept of "thermal governance" by linking architectural and technological as well as legal and economic dimensions of climate control in urban environments.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4a21. Jahrhundert. 4aChongqing. 4aGenf. 4aKairo. 4aMikroklima. 4aSantiago de Chile. 4aUrbanismus. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  a21st century.  aCairo.  aChongqing.  aGeneva.  aSantiago de Cile.  aUrbanism.  amicro climate.1 aEpiney, Lionel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhodbane, Dalila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKobi, Madlen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKobi, Madlen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRamakrishnan, Chandra